This paper deals with image segmentation using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of Bayesian deep learning also suggests a focus on uncertainty estimation, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves statistical analysis and modeling, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.MS). Finally, the use of deep learning models for segmentation suggests a possible connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
